isolation: isolate; is there to keep the z-index layering self-contained inside .hero-trails-video.

Without it, elements with z-index can sometimes interact with things outside the hero in weird ways, especially when you use negative z-index like this:



flex-shrink: 1; means: “yes, you can shrink me if needed”
flex-shrink: 0; means: “no, keep my size”

